Class Description
AllEndToEndTestResults
AllEndToEndTestResults is a custom object containing three Lists - validateModelResultsList, validateFormulaResultList, endToEndTestResultsList.
Arguments
Data type for storing the command line arguments for the Kripke filename, the optional state to check, the model input source (file/argument) and either the model filename or the model, depending on the model input source specified.
Controller
Runs end to end tests, reads input files, validates the model and formula, and runs the model checker
EndToEndFormulaFileObj
Data structure storing information from the end to end formula test files (the state to test, the formula and the expected result)
EndToEndTestResult
Data structure for storing the results of one end to end test.
EndToEndTestResultWithValidation  
FormulaInputSource
Enumerates the two ways the model string (ie, "EXp") can be provided to the program - 1) either hard coded as an command line argument when this program is run or 2) in a input text file containing the model string
Kripke
A data structure representing a Kripke structure.
KripkeFileObj
A bookkeeping data structure containing a Kripke object as well as all associated "meta data" such as the kripke file's original filepath, the states and transitions in the kripke, as well as any errors (including line numbers) that occurred while parsing the kripke file
Main  
Model
Holds the validation results and model check results (both for individual user entered models/formulas) and end to end test results The model is only used in runProgram in Controller.java where it stores the results of validation/model-checking/end-to-end-tests and then the model is immediately sent to the view.
ModelCheckInputs
The ModelCheckInputs class has four private properties - the first three are inputs to this class: Kripke, the state to check and the model.
ModelCheckResults
The results of a single model check run.
Options
Class with user set options.
ParseException
This exception is thrown when parse errors are encountered.
ParseException
This exception is thrown when parse errors are encountered.
Parser
The Parser class does the heavy lifting for the model checking and contains the SAT algorithms.
ParserConstants
Token literal values and constants.
ParserTokenManager
Token Manager.
SimpleCharStream
An implementation of interface CharStream, where the stream is assumed to contain only ASCII characters (without unicode processing).
SimpleCharStream
An implementation of interface CharStream, where the stream is assumed to contain only ASCII characters (without unicode processing).
State
Class for the state data type, representing a node in a directed graph.
TestFiles
Class for storing the names of the test files in an organized manner The test file directory has kripkes and models (both valid and invalid versions of both).
Token

Token

TokenMgrError
Token Manager Error.
TokenMgrError
Token Manager Error.
Transition
Class for the transition data type, representing a pair of states that are connected by an arrow in a directed graph.
Utils
Generic utility methods for dealing with States, Transitions, CTL labels, Sets and some other miscellaneous items.
ValidateFormulaResults
Data structure containing bookkeeping info on the results of validating a CTL formula (checking whether it is well formed.
ValidateModelResults
Data structure storing information on whether a model passed validation (had no syntax errors)
ValidateStateToCheckResults
Data structure holding the results of validating a state to check (checking if the state to check is in the model)
ValidationResults
Data structure holding the results of mode/formula/state validation.
Validator
The Validator class checks the syntax of the CTL formulas and makes sure they are well formed (contain no syntax errors).
ValidatorConstants
